# UI/UX Standards for Heatmap Application

## Visual Design Requirements

- **Background**: Pure white (#ffffff)
- **Grid lines**: Pure black (#000000) with 2px width
- **Heat colors**: Red gradient from white to full red
- **Typography**: Arial, sans-serif for clean readability

## User Interface Elements

### Canvas Area
- 600x600px canvas with crosshair cursor
- Subtle border and shadow for definition
- Rounded corners (8px border-radius)

### Control Panel
- Horizontal layout below canvas
- Clear button with primary blue styling (#007bff)
- Intensity controls with +/- buttons
- Real-time intensity value display

### Interactive Feedback
- Crosshair cursor over canvas area
- Hover effects on buttons (darker blue #0056b3)
- Smooth transitions (0.3s duration)
- Visual intensity indicator

## Responsive Design

- Center-aligned layout with flexbox
- Minimum viewport height (100vh)
- Consistent spacing (20px margins, 15px gaps)
- Mobile-friendly button sizes (minimum 44px touch targets)

## Accessibility Considerations

- Proper semantic HTML structure
- Descriptive button text
- Color contrast compliance
- Keyboard navigation support where applicable

## Information Architecture

- Clear heading hierarchy
- Instructional text below controls
- Intuitive control grouping
- Visual hierarchy with typography and spacing